This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a novel convolutional operator to improve the efficiency of convolutional neural networks. It may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it involves optimizing neural network architectures. Additionally, it could be categorized under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories as it involves optimizing the computational efficiency of multimedia-related tasks.
